tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine, suggesting possible renal impairment, and low total CO₂, which may indicate mild metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, raising suspicion for renal dysfunction and possible glycosuria unrelated to diabetes (low HbA1c). No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and consideration of non-diabetic causes for glucosuria.
